===Etymology===
From {{der|ja|ojp|-|sort=いう}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

{{IPAchar|/ipu/}} → {{IPAchar|/iɸu/}} → {{IPAchar|/*iwu/}} → {{IPAchar|/iu/}}

Medial {{IPAchar|/h/}} regularly changed from {{IPAchar|[p]}} → {{IPAchar|[ɸ]}} → {{IPAchar|[w]}}. Japanese never distinguished between {{IPAchar|/wu/}} and {{IPAchar|/u/}}, so that automatically becomes {{IPAchar|[u]}}. The {{IPAchar|/w/}} only surfaces in the negative form of ''i'''w'''anai'', where the phoneme {{IPAchar|/wa/}} exists. Surface forms {{IPAchar|/iwimasu/}} and {{IPAchar|/iwemasu/}} automatically become {{IPAchar|/iimasu/}} and {{IPAchar|/iemasu/}} since Japanese no longer distinguishes {{IPAchar|/wi, we/}} from {{IPAchar|/i, e/}}.

Possibly related to {{cog|ko|-}} {{ko-inline|입|ip|mouth}}.

