====Idioms====
{{der-top|Idioms}}
* {{ja-r|言う迄もない|いう まで も ない}}: it goes without saying
* {{ja-r|言うに及ばず|いう に およばず}}: it goes without saying; it isn't easy say {{qualifier|not reaching the point of being easily expressed}}
* {{ja-r|言うに足らず|いう に たらず}}: it isn't worth bringing up; it isn't easy to say {{qualifier|not sufficiently clear, not easily expressible}}
* {{ja-r|言わん方無し|いわん かた なし}}: no way of saying it
* {{ja-r|言わぬが花|いわぬ が はな}}: “not saying it, is a flower” → it would be better to leave it [[unsaid]]
* {{ja-r|言わずもがな|いわず も がな}}: “not even saying would be preferable” {{qualifier|either because it is already known and doesn't need saying, or because not expressing it at all would be better}}
